{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1066,"text":"Twenty-five years ago, scientists at CERN\ncreated the World Wide Web."},{"time":6174,"text":"Since then, the Internet has transformed \nthe way we communicate,"},{"time":10083,"text":"the way we do business,\nand even the way we live."},{"time":13545,"text":"In many ways,"},{"time":15717,"text":"the ideas that gave birth to Google,\nFacebook, Twitter, and so many others,"},{"time":20542,"text":"have now really transformed our lives,"},{"time":23146,"text":"and this has brought us many real benefits\nsuch as a more connected society."},{"time":27433,"text":"However, there are also\nsome downsides to this."},{"time":31134,"text":"Today, the average person\nhas an astounding amount"},{"time":33967,"text":"of personal information online,"},{"time":36080,"text":"and we add to this online information\nevery single time we post on Facebook,"},{"time":39737,"text":"each time we search on Google,"},{"time":41939,"text":"and each time we send an email."}]},{"cues":[{"time":44341,"text":"Now, many of us probably think,"},{"time":46343,"text":"well, one email,\nthere's nothing in there, right?"},{"time":49453,"text":"But if you consider\na year's worth of emails,"},{"time":52659,"text":"or maybe even a lifetime of email,"},{"time":55561,"text":"collectively, this tells a lot."},{"time":57907,"text":"It tells where we have been,\nwho we have met,"},{"time":61470,"text":"and in many ways,\neven what we're thinking about."},{"time":64709,"text":"And the more scary part about this is\nour data now lasts forever,"},{"time":69086,"text":"so your data can and will outlive you."},{"time":72093,"text":"What has happened is that we've largely\nlost control over our data"},{"time":75622,"text":"and also our privacy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":77944,"text":"So this year, as the web turns 25,"},{"time":81474,"text":"it's very important for us\nto take a moment"},{"time":83772,"text":"and think about the implications of this."},{"time":86304,"text":"We have to really think."},{"time":88006,"text":"We've lost privacy, yes,"},{"time":89796,"text":"but actually what we've also lost\nis the idea of privacy itself."},{"time":93995,"text":"If you think about it,"},{"time":95749,"text":"most of us here today probably remember \nwhat life was like before the Internet,"},{"time":99763,"text":"but today, there's a new generation"},{"time":102305,"text":"that is being taught from a very young age\nto share everything online,"},{"time":105725,"text":"and this is a generation that is not \ngoing to remember when data was private."},{"time":110204,"text":"So we keep going down this road,\n20 years from now,"},{"time":113592,"text":"the word 'privacy' is going to have\na completely different meaning"},{"time":116688,"text":"from what it means to you and I."}]},{"cues":[{"time":118973,"text":"So, it's time for us \nto take a moment and think,"},{"time":121413,"text":"is there anything we can do about this?"},{"time":124220,"text":"And I believe there is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":126705,"text":"Let's take a look at one of the most\nwidely used forms of communication"},{"time":130266,"text":"in the world today: email."},{"time":132533,"text":"Before the invention of email,\nwe largely communicated using letters,"},{"time":136294,"text":"and the process was quite simple."},{"time":138616,"text":"You would first start by writing\nyour message on a piece of paper,"},{"time":141728,"text":"then you would place it\ninto a sealed envelope,"},{"time":144132,"text":"and from there,\nyou would go ahead and send it"},{"time":146387,"text":"after you put a stamp and address on it."},{"time":148345,"text":"Unfortunately, today,"},{"time":149825,"text":"when we actually send an email,\nwe're not sending a letter."},{"time":152642,"text":"What you are sending, in many ways,\nis actually a postcard,"},{"time":155417,"text":"and it's a postcard in the sense\nthat everybody that sees it"},{"time":159064,"text":"from the time it leaves your computer\nto when it gets to the recipient"},{"time":162699,"text":"can actually read the entire contents."}]},{"cues":[{"time":165319,"text":"So, the solution to this\nhas been known for some time,"},{"time":168778,"text":"and there's many attempts to do it."},{"time":170621,"text":"The most basic solution\nis to use encryption,"},{"time":173770,"text":"and the idea is quite simple."},{"time":175697,"text":"First, you encrypt the connection"},{"time":177466,"text":"between your computer\nand the email server."},{"time":180074,"text":"Then, you also encrypt the data\nas it sits on the server itself."},{"time":183700,"text":"But there's a problem with this,"},{"time":185646,"text":"and that is, the email servers\nalso hold the encryption keys,"},{"time":188595,"text":"so now you have a really big lock\nwith a key placed right next to it."},{"time":192980,"text":"But not only that, any government\ncould lawfully ask for"},{"time":196211,"text":"and get the key to your data,"},{"time":198441,"text":"and this is all without you\nbeing aware of it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":201064,"text":"So the way we fix this problem\nis actually relatively easy, in principle:"},{"time":206337,"text":"You give everybody their own keys,"},{"time":208739,"text":"and then you make sure the server\ndoesn't actually have the keys."},{"time":212012,"text":"This seems like common sense, right?"},{"time":214148,"text":"So the question that comes up is,\nwhy hasn't this been done yet?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":218261,"text":"Well, if we really think about it,"},{"time":220796,"text":"we see that the business model\nof the Internet today"},{"time":223721,"text":"really isn't compatible with privacy."},{"time":225788,"text":"Just take a look at some\nof the biggest names on the web,"},{"time":228574,"text":"and you see that advertising\nplays a huge role."},{"time":231501,"text":"In fact, this year alone,\nadvertising is 137 billion dollars,"},{"time":236329,"text":"and to optimize the ads\nthat are shown to us,"},{"time":238500,"text":"companies have to know\neverything about us."},{"time":240633,"text":"They need to know where we live,"},{"time":242552,"text":"how old we are, what we like,\nwhat we don't like,"},{"time":246207,"text":"and anything else\nthey can get their hands on."},{"time":248369,"text":"And if you think about it,"},{"time":250098,"text":"the best way to get this information\nis really just to invade our privacy."},{"time":254246,"text":"So these companies\naren't going to give us our privacy."},{"time":257437,"text":"If we want to have privacy online,"},{"time":259252,"text":"what we have to do is\nwe've got to go out and get it ourselves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":262795,"text":"For many years, when it came to email,"},{"time":265063,"text":"the only solution\nwas something known as PGP,"},{"time":267978,"text":"which was quite complicated\nand only accessible to the tech-savvy."},{"time":271192,"text":"Here's a diagram that basically shows"},{"time":273610,"text":"the process for encrypting\nand decrypting messages."},{"time":276345,"text":"So needless to say,\nthis is not a solution for everybody,"},{"time":279231,"text":"and this actually is part of the problem,"},{"time":282363,"text":"because if you think about communication,"},{"time":284825,"text":"by definition, it involves\nhaving someone to communicate with."},{"time":289180,"text":"So while PGP does a great job\nof what it's designed to do,"},{"time":292394,"text":"for the people out there\nwho can't understand how to use it,"},{"time":295215,"text":"the option to communicate privately\nsimply does not exist."},{"time":298117,"text":"And this is a problem\nthat we need to solve."},{"time":301125,"text":"So if we want to have privacy online,"},{"time":303123,"text":"the only way we can succeed\nis if we get the whole world on board,"},{"time":306442,"text":"and this is only possible\nif we bring down the barrier to entry."},{"time":309693,"text":"I think this is actually the key challenge\nthat lies in the tech community."},{"time":313222,"text":"What we really have to do\nis work and make privacy more accessible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":317285,"text":"So last summer, when\nthe Edward Snowden story came out,"},{"time":320281,"text":"several colleagues and I decided to see\nif we could make this happen."},{"time":323896,"text":"At that time, we were working at the\nEuropean Organization for Nuclear Research"},{"time":328883,"text":"at the world's largest particle collider,\nwhich collides protons, by the way."},{"time":332614,"text":"We were all scientists,\nso we used our scientific creativity"},{"time":336059,"text":"and came up with a very\ncreative name for our project:"},{"time":339293,"text":"ProtonMail.\n(Laughter)"},{"time":341389,"text":"Many startups these days\nactually begin in people's garages"},{"time":344257,"text":"or people's basements."},{"time":345941,"text":"We were a bit different."},{"time":347438,"text":"We started out at the CERN cafeteria,"},{"time":350081,"text":"which actually is great, because look,"},{"time":352537,"text":"you have all the food\nand water you could ever want."},{"time":355010,"text":"But even better than this\nis that every day"},{"time":357490,"text":"between 12 p.m. and 2 p.m.,\nfree of charge,"},{"time":361461,"text":"the CERN cafeteria comes with\nseveral thousand scientists and engineers,"},{"time":365710,"text":"and these guys basically know\nthe answers to everything."},{"time":368496,"text":"So it was in this environment\nthat we began working."},{"time":371283,"text":"What we actually want to do\nis we want to take your email"},{"time":374394,"text":"and turn it into something\nthat looks more like this,"},{"time":377854,"text":"but more importantly,\nwe want to do it in a way"},{"time":380129,"text":"that you can't even tell\nthat it's happened."},{"time":382274,"text":"So to do this, we actually need\na combination of technology"},{"time":385261,"text":"and also design."}]},{"cues":[{"time":386848,"text":"So how do we go about\ndoing something like this?"},{"time":390018,"text":"Well, it's probably a good idea\nnot to put the keys on the server."},{"time":394172,"text":"So what we do is we generate\nencryption keys on your computer,"},{"time":398070,"text":"and we don't generate a single key,\nbut actually a pair of keys,"},{"time":401858,"text":"so there's an RSA private key\nand an RSA public key,"},{"time":405563,"text":"and these keys\nare mathematically connected."}]},{"cues":[{"time":408191,"text":"So let's have a look\nand see how this works"},{"time":410396,"text":"when multiple people communicate."},{"time":412787,"text":"So here we have Bob and Alice,\nwho want to communicate privately."},{"time":417232,"text":"So the key challenge\nis to take Bob's message"},{"time":420794,"text":"and to get it to Alice in such a way\nthat the server cannot read that message."},{"time":425103,"text":"So what we have to do\nis we have to encrypt it"},{"time":427516,"text":"before it even leaves Bob's computer,"},{"time":429640,"text":"and one of the tricks is, we encrypt it\nusing the public key from Alice."},{"time":434141,"text":"Now this encrypted data is sent\nthrough the server to Alice,"},{"time":439333,"text":"and because the message was encrypted\nusing Alice's public key,"},{"time":443613,"text":"the only key that can now decrypt it\nis a private key that belongs to Alice,"},{"time":447901,"text":"and it turns out Alice is the only person\nthat actually has this key."},{"time":452616,"text":"So we've now accomplished the objective,"},{"time":455284,"text":"which is to get the message\nfrom Bob to Alice"},{"time":457451,"text":"without the server being able\nto read what's going on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":460143,"text":"Actually, what I've shown here\nis a highly simplified picture."},{"time":463100,"text":"The reality is much more complex"},{"time":465105,"text":"and it requires a lot of software\nthat looks a bit like this."},{"time":468819,"text":"And that's actually\nthe key design challenge:"},{"time":471259,"text":"How do we take all this complexity,\nall this software,"},{"time":474780,"text":"and implement it in a way\nthat the user cannot see it."},{"time":478898,"text":"I think with ProtonMail,\nwe have gotten pretty close to doing this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":482496,"text":"So let's see how it works in practice."},{"time":484958,"text":"Here, we've got Bob and Alice again,"},{"time":487975,"text":"who also want to communicate securely."},{"time":489945,"text":"They simply create accounts on ProtonMail,"},{"time":492132,"text":"which is quite simple\nand takes a few moments,"},{"time":494542,"text":"and all the key encryption and generation"},{"time":496964,"text":"is happening automatically\nin the background"},{"time":499354,"text":"as Bob is creating his account."},{"time":501060,"text":"Once his account is created,\nhe just clicks \"compose,\""},{"time":503602,"text":"and now he can write his email\nlike he does today."},{"time":506589,"text":"So he fills in his information,"},{"time":508456,"text":"and then after that, \nall he has to do is click \"send,\""},{"time":511740,"text":"and just like that,\nwithout understanding cryptography,"},{"time":515281,"text":"and without doing anything different\nfrom how he writes email today,"},{"time":518834,"text":"Bob has just sent an encrypted message."}]},{"cues":[{"time":521481,"text":"What we have here\nis really just the first step,"},{"time":525593,"text":"but it shows that\nwith improving technology,"},{"time":527890,"text":"privacy doesn't have to be difficult,\nit doesn't have to be disruptive."},{"time":532065,"text":"If we change the goal from maximizing \nad revenue to protecting data,"},{"time":536512,"text":"we can actually make it accessible."},{"time":539008,"text":"Now, I know a question\non everybody's minds is,"},{"time":541468,"text":"okay, protecting privacy,\nthis is a great goal,"},{"time":543858,"text":"but can you actually do this"},{"time":546298,"text":"without the tons of money\nthat advertisements give you?"},{"time":549090,"text":"And I think the answer is actually yes,"},{"time":551476,"text":"because today, we've reached a point"},{"time":553706,"text":"where people around the world really\nunderstand how important privacy is,"},{"time":557652,"text":"and when you have that,\nanything is possible."},{"time":560625,"text":"Earlier this year,"},{"time":561789,"text":"ProtonMail actually had so many users \nthat we ran out of resources,"},{"time":565454,"text":"and when this happened,\nour community of users got together"},{"time":568283,"text":"and donated half a million dollars."},{"time":570399,"text":"So this is just an example\nof what can happen"},{"time":572830,"text":"when you bring the community together\ntowards a common goal."},{"time":575643,"text":"We can also leverage the world."},{"time":577449,"text":"Right now,"},{"time":578597,"text":"we have a quarter of a million people\nthat have signed up for ProtonMail,"},{"time":582023,"text":"and these people come from everywhere,"},{"time":583832,"text":"and this really shows that privacy"},{"time":585464,"text":"is not just an American\nor a European issue,"},{"time":587716,"text":"it's a global issue\nthat impacts all of us."},{"time":590061,"text":"It's something that we really\nhave to pay attention to going forward."}]},{"cues":[{"time":593521,"text":"So what do we have to do\nto solve this problem?"},{"time":596517,"text":"Well, first of all,"},{"time":598514,"text":"we need to support a different\nbusiness model for the Internet,"},{"time":601508,"text":"one that does not rely\nentirely on advertisements"},{"time":603841,"text":"for revenue and for growth."},{"time":606175,"text":"We actually need to build a new Internet"},{"time":608684,"text":"where our privacy and our ability \nto control our data is first and foremost."},{"time":614377,"text":"But even more importantly,"},{"time":616122,"text":"we have to build an Internet \nwhere privacy is no longer just an option"},{"time":620990,"text":"but is also the default."}]},{"cues":[{"time":623923,"text":"We have done the first step\nwith ProtonMail,"},{"time":626493,"text":"but this is really just the first step\nin a very, very long journey."},{"time":630074,"text":"The good news I can share\nwith you guys today,"},{"time":632997,"text":"the exciting news,\nis that we're not traveling alone."},{"time":635525,"text":"The movement to protect people's privacy\nand freedom online"},{"time":638375,"text":"is really gaining momentum,"},{"time":639861,"text":"and today, there are dozens of projects\nfrom all around the world"},{"time":643455,"text":"who are working together\nto improve our privacy."},{"time":646966,"text":"These projects protect things\nfrom our chat to voice communications,"},{"time":650612,"text":"also our file storage, our online search,"},{"time":653416,"text":"our online browsing,\nand many other things."},{"time":656457,"text":"And these projects are not backed\nby billions of dollars in advertising,"},{"time":659986,"text":"but they've found support\nreally from the people,"},{"time":662309,"text":"from private individuals like you and I\nfrom all over the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":665356,"text":"This really matters, because ultimately,"},{"time":668473,"text":"privacy depends on each\nand every one of us,"},{"time":671944,"text":"and we have to protect it now\nbecause our online data"},{"time":674777,"text":"is more than just a collection\nof ones and zeros."},{"time":677541,"text":"It's actually a lot more than that."},{"time":679397,"text":"It's our lives, our personal stories,"},{"time":681743,"text":"our friends, our families,"},{"time":684041,"text":"and in many ways,\nalso our hopes and our aspirations."},{"time":687547,"text":"We need to spend time now\nto really protect our right"},{"time":690651,"text":"to share this only with people\nthat we want to share this with,"},{"time":693601,"text":"because without this,\nwe simply can't have a free society."},{"time":696341,"text":"So now's the time for us\nto collectively stand up and say,"},{"time":699194,"text":"yes, we do want to live\nin a world with online privacy,"},{"time":702687,"text":"and yes, we can work together\nto turn this vision into a reality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":707215,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":709350,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}